node.text:
What are you reading this weekend?📚

Want to know what's on Eggleston's stack? Eggleston is reading books that foster a #GrowthMindset! The growth mindset is the belief that you can grow your brain and that your intelligence grows when you challenge yourself and work hard to learn new things.

Check out these two books Eggleston recommends ⬇️

📕 The Watsons Go to Birmingham — 1963 by Christopher Paul Curtis. Ten-year-old Kenny lives with his family in Michigan. His teenage brother Byron gets into too much trouble, so his family heads south to visit their grandmother in Alabama. Grandma is the one person who can get Byron into shape. It’s 1963, and they are in town when Grandma’s church is blown up.

📘 The Hate U Give by Angie Thomas. 16-year-old Starr Carter goes to a rich, fancy, school where most of the kids are white, but she lives in a neighborhood where most of her neighbors are Black. She suddenly finds her worlds colliding when she witnesses the fatal police shooting of her best friend, Khalil, an unarmed Black teen.

Have you read these books? What did you think?

node.text:
Summer is the perfect time for HOBBIES. So we want to know - what's a hobby you've wanted to try but haven't yet?

Our Facebook and Twitter followers said they wanted to try:
🌟 Stargazing
📷 Photography
🌊 Paddle boarding
💻 Coding
🎨 Drawing
🎤 Public speaking

What about you? Tell us in the comments. Maybe this can be the summer that you get started!

With #CampKhan you only spend 15-minutes a day doing math on Khan Academy and the rest of the day is yours for hobbies and anything else! ✨ (Plus you can win cool prizes - get more details in the link in our bio). 🔗

We saved you last year.😌 We're here for you this year.💖

Want to head into the new school year with confidence? Practice 15 minutes a day on Khan Academy with #CampKhan, a 31-day challenge during July! 

Fill out the #CampKhan2021 tracker each day and share photos of your progress for more than 20 chances to win airpods, bluetooth speakers, hydroflasks, a national park annual pass, and more throughout July. 🎉 Get the tracker and info on how to win prizes at the link in our bio.🔗

I'm just going to check my notifications...

This ever happen to you? Suddenly 1, 2, or 3 hours pass and you're still scrolling? 🙄🙃

Tomorrow we are kicking off #CampKhan! It's a 31-day challenge during July! You spend just 15 minutes a day on Khan Academy and the rest of the day is yours - to be screen free and enjoy your break.✨ Those 15 minutes will give you confidence for math class next year and a major flex if you win some of our prizes. 😎💪

You can win the first prize RIGHT NOW! 😮 Win a Khan Academy Hydroflask by downloading the challenge tracker, writing down your goal for #CampKhan2021, and uploading your tracker at the link in our bio. Enter by July 1 at 11:59 pm PT! Full rules available at the link. 🚰🔗

UPDATE: Congrats to Nirvan for winning the Hydro Flask. There's still lots of prizes to win!!

Fill out the tracker each day and share photos of your progress for more than 20 chances to win airpods, bluetooth speakers, a national park annual pass, and more throughout July. 🎉 Tag a friend who you think would want one of those prizes! 💖

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Khan Academy on June 28, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says '* Pi Tau'.

node.text:
Happy Tau Day! Who is Tau, you ask? 👀

In the U.S. a lot of people celebrate Pi day on 3/14 (March 14) because π is approximately equal to 3.14. 🥧

Some mathematicians argue that the beloved constant π is the wrong choice of circle constant and instead we should use an alternate constant equal to 2π and use the Greek letter tau. Tau is approximately equal to 6.28, so that makes today (6/28) Tau Day!

We don't think Pi should get all of the attention. So today we want to honor Tau!

One way to celebrate? Eat twice as much pie as you would on Pi Day! 🥧🥧 Another way to celebrate? Learn about Pi and Tau at the link in our bio.🔗

[Photo: two people sit in a car. In the passenger seat one individual is wearing a flamboyant costume with a lot of bright pink boas and feathers, yellow square sunglasses, and a feathered hat. Underneath this person is the text, Pi. In the driver seat, an individual wears a very plain black shirt and is looking toward the pink feathers. Underneath this person is the text, Tau.]

They're good dogs, yall.🥺🐕

Today is #TakeYourDogToWorkDay and for the past 16 months we've been working from home with our doggos always close by.💖 We're a learning organization, so we asked the team to share a lesson their dog has taught them.🤔 Meet nine very good dogs and learn nine very good lessons.⬇️

🐶 Balthasar taught me to value and prioritize time spent at home with my loved ones.

🐕 Jackson taught me to live in the moment, give and receive love, and that naps are good.

🐩 Rey has taught (and teaches!) me to live every day with joy in my heart. 

🐶  CJ taught me that it’s about whatever works for YOU not anyone else (see strange pose he finds comfortable, perched on my knee??) and that life’s great moments are always happening.

🐕 Astra teaches me the joy of being out in nature.

🐩 Phryne has taught us that it’s okay to be exhausted. It’s important to take care of yourself!

🐶 Pistachio has taught me that positive learning environments encourage curiosity and success. 

🐕 Max taught me you can't buy love but you can rescue it. Tyler taught me to share space.

What's a lesson your dog has taught you?

#DailyFluff #DogsOfInstagram #GoodDogs #DailyWoof
